# Testing Conventions

- Use `unittest.TestCase` with `self.assert*` methods.
- Use `tempfile.TemporaryDirectory` for any test that touches the filesystem.
- Use `self.subTest()` for parameterised assertions.
- Test names: `test_<what_it_verifies>` (e.g. `test_label_normalisation_uses_canonical_config_names`).
- Test classes: `<Feature>Tests` (e.g. `XbdParsingTests`, `ManifestTests`).
- Keep tests focused — one logical assertion per test method.
- Do not import or depend on raw xBD data. Create synthetic fixtures.
- Run with: `python -m unittest discover -s tests`
